# LYRA Audit System Context

This project uses the LYRA v1.1 multi-agent audit system. Key files:

- `audits/open_findings.json` -- canonical current state of all findings
- `audits/index.json` -- run history
- `audits/findings/*.md` -- per-finding case files with history
- `audits/prompts/*.md` -- agent prompts (paste-and-run)
- `audits/schema/audit-output.schema.json` -- JSON Schema v1.1.0

## Enum Rules (strict)

When creating or modifying audit findings, use ONLY these values:

- severity: blocker | major | minor | nit
- priority: P0 | P1 | P2 | P3
- type: bug | enhancement | debt | question
- status: open | accepted | in_progress | fixed_pending_verify | fixed_verified | wont_fix | deferred | duplicate | converted_to_enhancement
- confidence: evidence | inference | speculation
- estimated_effort: trivial | small | medium | large | epic

## Finding ID Format

`f-` + first 8 hex chars of SHA-256 of `type|category|file_path|symbol|title`.
Fallback: `f-<category>-<file_slug>-<NNN>` (max 50 characters).

## When the user asks about audits

- Check `audits/open_findings.json` for current state
- Check `audits/findings/<id>.md` for history on specific findings
- Reference `audits/prompts/` for available agent prompts
- Use `python3 audits/session.py` for workflow guidance
